  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 7 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV). Across base airports: 2 critical, 9 high, 10 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV); plus 8 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and RVR limitations  — most notably around Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV). Network hotspots: Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Stavanger Airport, Sola (SVG/ENZV) and 2 others. Primary drivers: approach minima limits, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Stavanger Airport, Sola (SVG/ENZV) and 9 others.",
